HEADWORD: Hamamelidanthum
<hw>Hamamelidanthum</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A genus of fossil plants of
the Oligocene having flowers resembling those of the witch hazel; found
in Baltic region.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Hamamelidanthum</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
